  "prompt": "Did islam exist before prophet mohmmad?",
  "response": "Islam, as a distinct religious tradition, emerged in the 7th century CE with the prophet Muhammad, who is considered the final prophet of Islam. However, the term \"Islam\" itself means \"submission\" (to the will of God), and the roots of the faith can be traced back to earlier religious traditions, particularly those of Judaism and Christianity, as well as the religious practices of pre-Islamic Arabia.\n\nIn a broader sense, many Muslims believe that all prophets preached a form of Islam \u2014 submission to the one true God \u2014 even before the time of Muhammad. This perspective encompasses figures such as Abraham, Moses, and Jesus, who are also recognized as prophets in Islam.\n\nBefore the formal establishment of Islam as a structured religion through Muhammad's teachings, the Arabian Peninsula had diverse religious beliefs, including polytheism, Judaism, and Christianity, along with various tribal religions. Thus, while the specific religious practices and beliefs of Islam as a distinct religion began with Muhammad, the idea of submission to God and the worship of one God has ancient roots that precede him.",
